  24:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****                     ##### IWDG Generic features #####
  25:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****   [..]
  27:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (+) The IWDG can be started by either software or hardware (configurable
  28:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         through option byte).
  29:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
ARM GAS  /tmp/cc4zWoWL.s 			page 2


  30:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (+) The IWDG is clocked by the Low-Speed Internal clock (LSI) and thus stays
  31:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         active even if the main clock fails.
  32:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  33:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (+) Once the IWDG is started, the LSI is forced ON and both cannot be
  34:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         disabled. The counter starts counting down from the reset value (0xFFF).
  35:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         When it reaches the end of count value (0x000) a reset signal is
  36:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         generated (IWDG reset).
  37:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  38:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (+) Whenever the key value 0x0000 AAAA is written in the IWDG_KR register,
  39:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         the IWDG_RLR value is reloaded into the counter and the watchdog reset
  40:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         is prevented.
  41:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  42:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (+) The IWDG is implemented in the VDD voltage domain that is still functional
  43:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         in STOP and STANDBY mode (IWDG reset can wake up the CPU from STANDBY).
  44:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         IWDGRST flag in RCC_CSR register can be used to inform when an IWDG
  45:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         reset occurs.
  46:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  47:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (+) Debug mode: When the microcontroller enters debug mode (core halted),
  48:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         the IWDG counter either continues to work normally or stops, depending
  49:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         on DBG_IWDG_STOP configuration bit in DBG module, accessible through
  50:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         __HAL_DBGMCU_FREEZE_IWDG() and __HAL_DBGMCU_UNFREEZE_IWDG() macros.
  51:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  52:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     [..] Min-max timeout value @32KHz (LSI): ~125us / ~32.7s
  53:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          The IWDG timeout may vary due to LSI clock frequency dispersion.
  54:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          STM32F4xx devices provide the capability to measure the LSI clock
  55:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          frequency (LSI clock is internally connected to TIM5 CH4 input capture).
  56:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          The measured value can be used to have an IWDG timeout with an
  57:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          acceptable accuracy.
  58:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  59:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     [..] Default timeout value (necessary for IWDG_SR status register update):
  60:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          Constant LSI_VALUE is defined based on the nominal LSI clock frequency.
  61:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          This frequency being subject to variations as mentioned above, the
  62:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          default timeout value (defined through constant HAL_IWDG_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT
  63:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          below) may become too short or too long.
  64:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          In such cases, this default timeout value can be tuned by redefining
  65:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          the constant LSI_VALUE at user-application level (based, for instance,
  66:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****          on the measured LSI clock frequency as explained above).
  67:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  68:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****                      ##### How to use this driver #####
  69:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****   ==============================================================================
  70:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****   [..]
  71:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (#) Use IWDG using HAL_IWDG_Init() function to :
  72:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****       (++) Enable instance by writing Start keyword in IWDG_KEY register. LSI
  73:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****            clock is forced ON and IWDG counter starts counting down.
  74:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****       (++) Enable write access to configuration registers:
  75:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****           IWDG_PR and IWDG_RLR.
  76:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****       (++) Configure the IWDG prescaler and counter reload value. This reload
  77:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****            value will be loaded in the IWDG counter each time the watchdog is
  78:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****            reloaded, then the IWDG will start counting down from this value.
  79:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****       (++) Wait for status flags to be reset.
  80:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
  81:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****     (#) Then the application program must refresh the IWDG counter at regular
  82:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         intervals during normal operation to prevent an MCU reset, using
  83:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c ****         HAL_IWDG_Refresh() function.
  84:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_iwdg.c **** 
